overview: When Finnish artists Oliver Kochta-Kalleinen and Tellervo Kalleinen decided to examine how people complain about their woes -- large and small -- they created a worldwide phenomenon, as captured in this humorous documentary. After finding ordinary citizens and crafting their complaints into song, the pair turns the volunteers into a choir that performs for the community, but when they travel to Singapore, government officials forbid their concert.
title: Complaints Choir
